File: Ten more deaths have also been recorded, bringing the total to 75. JOHANNESBURG - The number of coronavirus cases has risen by 318, Health Minister Zweli Mkhize said on Thursday night. The total number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in South Africa is now 3,953. COVID-19: Dis-Chem charged for inflating prices "We are observing the steady increase in the number positive cases. While this is concerning, we are also pleased that the intensified community screening and testing campaign is assisting in finding more COVID-19 positive patients", said Mkhize. Ten more deaths have also been recorded, bringing the total to 75. Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.